1
00:00:13,010 --> 00:00:15,810
[Episode 9]

2
00:00:32,015 --> 00:00:33,134
Why are you kneeling here?

3
00:00:33,735 --> 00:00:34,614
Second Young Master.

4
00:00:36,855 --> 00:00:38,094
Your mother is punishing me.

5
00:00:38,735 --> 00:00:39,574
My mother?

6
00:00:40,615 --> 00:00:41,734
Why is she punishing you?

7
00:00:42,375 --> 00:00:43,614
She punished me for treason.

8
00:00:45,015 --> 00:00:46,414
For being shameless.

9
00:00:47,815 --> 00:00:48,934
Second Young Master,

10
00:00:49,495 --> 00:00:50,654
Please don't blame me.

11
00:00:51,575 --> 00:00:52,814
This is what I deserve.

12
00:00:52,815 --> 00:00:53,654
Go back to your room first.

13
00:00:54,535 --> 00:00:55,454
As for my mother,

14
00:00:56,015 --> 00:00:57,494
I'll handle it with her.

15
00:00:57,575 --> 00:00:58,974
Second Young Master,

16
00:00:59,655 --> 00:01:01,214
please don't meddle in my affairs.

17
00:01:01,575 --> 00:01:03,094
Then at least hold an umbrella.

18
00:01:03,815 --> 00:01:04,974
Don't freeze yourself.

19
00:01:05,615 --> 00:01:06,574
Second Young Master,

20
00:01:08,215 --> 00:01:09,934
please mind your boundaries

21
00:01:10,335 --> 00:01:11,294
and status.

22
00:01:11,975 --> 00:01:13,254
Stop causing me trouble.

23
00:01:16,775 --> 00:01:17,414
Fine.

24
00:01:42,455 --> 00:01:43,014
Mother.

25
00:01:54,095 --> 00:01:55,174
This snow tonight

26
00:01:56,255 --> 00:01:58,094
won't stop anytime soon.

27
00:01:58,095 --> 00:01:59,374
If Fifth Concubine falls ill,

28
00:01:59,815 --> 00:02:00,814
it could damage your reputation

29
00:02:01,255 --> 00:02:03,014
if this were to get out.

30
00:02:05,295 --> 00:02:06,454
Tonight's punishment

31
00:02:06,455 --> 00:02:08,014
was ordered by the Master.

32
00:02:08,295 --> 00:02:09,894
Fifth concubine must be disciplined.

33
00:02:10,255 --> 00:02:11,254
Stay out of it.

34
00:02:12,895 --> 00:02:13,814
Could you have someone

35
00:02:13,975 --> 00:02:14,974
hold an umbrella for her,

36
00:02:15,375 --> 00:02:16,334
so she doesn't...

37
00:02:25,535 --> 00:02:26,254
Chen,

38
00:02:26,935 --> 00:02:28,094
you've crossed the line.

39
00:02:33,695 --> 00:02:35,734
I don't care what little schemes you have,

40
00:02:36,415 --> 00:02:37,974
keep them well hidden.

41
00:02:39,615 --> 00:02:41,854
Don't let observant people notice.

42
00:02:42,975 --> 00:02:45,214
You should know where my boundaries lie.

43
00:02:45,855 --> 00:02:47,054
Do you understand?

44
00:02:49,255 --> 00:02:50,254
Do you understand?

45
00:02:52,535 --> 00:02:53,534
I understand, Mother.

46
00:02:58,415 --> 00:03:00,094
Don't forget the hardships

47
00:03:00,095 --> 00:03:01,494
and humiliations we endured.

48
00:03:02,535 --> 00:03:04,534
Now that we've finally gained all this,

49
00:03:05,655 --> 00:03:07,974
I won't tolerate any loss.

50
00:03:08,855 --> 00:03:10,974
No matter the cost.

51
00:03:16,615 --> 00:03:18,694
Return to your room and rest tonight.

52
00:03:19,055 --> 00:03:20,334
Without my permission,

53
00:03:20,615 --> 00:03:21,734
don't come out.

54
00:03:23,855 --> 00:03:24,494
Yes.

55
00:03:26,655 --> 00:03:27,774
Shanghai tea market:

56
00:03:28,375 --> 00:03:29,614
500 crates of Longjing,

57
00:03:30,135 --> 00:03:31,134
30,000 silver dollars.

58
00:03:32,695 --> 00:03:33,894
Tianjin British Concession:

59
00:03:34,175 --> 00:03:35,294
1,000 crates of Longjing,

60
00:03:35,615 --> 00:03:36,614
60,000 silver dollars.

61
00:03:36,695 --> 00:03:37,254
And then...

62
00:03:37,935 --> 00:03:38,494
Master!

63
00:03:38,615 --> 00:03:39,574
The dock is on fire!

64
00:03:39,935 --> 00:03:40,534
What?

65
00:03:41,415 --> 00:03:42,214
To the dock!

66
00:04:06,055 --> 00:04:06,694
What are you doing?

67
00:04:07,335 --> 00:04:08,094
Stop it!

68
00:04:08,255 --> 00:04:09,134
There are people here!

69
00:04:17,775 --> 00:04:18,534
Get away!

70
00:04:19,655 --> 00:04:20,374
Apply medicine.

71
00:04:20,375 --> 00:04:21,214
I don't want to.

72
00:04:22,535 --> 00:04:23,694
So fierce with me,

73
00:04:24,135 --> 00:04:25,134
but like an innocent lamb

74
00:04:25,135 --> 00:04:26,254
when facing Third Concubine?

75
00:04:27,095 --> 00:04:27,934
I have my own goals.

76
00:04:28,175 --> 00:04:28,974
None of your business.

77
00:04:29,095 --> 00:04:29,974
Your goal?

78
00:04:30,175 --> 00:04:31,974
Making yourself sick is your goal?

79
00:04:32,055 --> 00:04:32,534
Yes.

80
00:04:33,095 --> 00:04:33,614
So

81
00:04:33,935 --> 00:04:35,134
you'd better not stop me.

82
00:04:36,935 --> 00:04:38,254
I know you're trying to fool them.

83
00:04:38,255 --> 00:04:39,774
Must it really come to this?

84
00:04:40,415 --> 00:04:41,054
Don't worry.

85
00:04:41,255 --> 00:04:42,054
There's a fire at the wharf.

86
00:04:42,055 --> 00:04:43,294
Everyone in the mansion is helping out.

87
00:04:43,695 --> 00:04:45,174
Nanxi is keeping an eye on Third Concubine.

88
00:04:45,375 --> 00:04:46,974
I ordered the backyard lights extinguished.

89
00:04:47,415 --> 00:04:48,603
Set up a scarecrow kneeling there.

90
00:04:48,627 --> 00:04:49,654
In this blizzard.

91
00:04:49,935 --> 00:04:51,174
No one will notice.

92
00:04:51,215 --> 00:04:53,094
A wharf fire in heavy snow?

93
00:04:53,975 --> 00:04:54,734
Your doing?

94
00:04:55,295 --> 00:04:56,174
So what if it is?

95
00:04:56,615 --> 00:04:57,494
Zhou Yimo.

96
00:04:57,855 --> 00:04:59,094
You're too arrogant.

97
00:04:59,175 --> 00:05:00,174
Aren't you the same?

98
00:05:00,335 --> 00:05:01,534
Look at your knees.

99
00:05:01,655 --> 00:05:03,374
Still think you're invincible?

100
00:05:21,735 --> 00:05:22,814
You're truly a medical student.

101
00:05:23,055 --> 00:05:24,014
So professional.

102
00:05:33,295 --> 00:05:34,294
Stop interfering my affairs, okay?

103
00:05:34,855 --> 00:05:35,974
my affairs, okay?

104
00:05:40,415 --> 00:05:41,814
Seems you still don't understand.

105
00:05:41,975 --> 00:05:42,974
Understand what?

106
00:05:45,055 --> 00:05:45,974
Three years ago,

107
00:05:46,415 --> 00:05:47,854
You saved my life at medical school.

108
00:05:48,655 --> 00:05:51,174
I'm only repaying that debt.

109
00:05:56,615 --> 00:05:57,374
What?

110
00:05:57,735 --> 00:05:58,974
Not surprised at all?

111
00:06:03,455 --> 00:06:04,614
I recognized you long ago.

112
00:06:41,735 --> 00:06:42,934
You clearly recognized me.

113
00:06:43,255 --> 00:06:44,494
Why didn't you acknowledge me?

114
00:06:45,175 --> 00:06:46,414
I changed my name.

115
00:06:47,735 --> 00:06:49,174
To assume a new identity.

116
00:06:49,175 --> 00:06:50,374
Why complicate things?

117
00:06:50,815 --> 00:06:52,054
Even if you're an opium destruction hero.

118
00:06:52,615 --> 00:06:53,654
Even if I saved you.

119
00:06:54,415 --> 00:06:56,734
It's useless to me now.

120
00:07:00,415 --> 00:07:01,534
You...

121
00:07:01,935 --> 00:07:03,454
have a heart of stone!

122
00:07:05,175 --> 00:07:06,614
Not everyone can live

123
00:07:06,615 --> 00:07:07,854
as freely as you do.

124
00:07:09,415 --> 00:07:11,174
The gracious young master by daylight.

125
00:07:12,415 --> 00:07:13,814
Wearing a mask by night.

126
00:07:14,415 --> 00:07:15,494
Fighting evil.

127
00:07:16,175 --> 00:07:17,014
Being a hero.

128
00:07:19,095 --> 00:07:20,774
Not some opium destruction hero.

129
00:07:21,495 --> 00:07:22,654
Newspapers often sensationalize the news

130
00:07:22,655 --> 00:07:24,134
to attract readers.

131
00:07:24,935 --> 00:07:26,294
Not the full truth.

132
00:07:26,735 --> 00:07:27,854
So what's the full truth?

133
00:07:29,495 --> 00:07:32,174
When the time is right, you'll be the first to know.

134
00:07:33,295 --> 00:07:33,814
By the way,

135
00:07:34,535 --> 00:07:35,694
I've found a lead

136
00:07:36,255 --> 00:07:37,814
about your sister's death.

137
00:07:40,175 --> 00:07:42,254
Wanted to tell you after investigating.

138
00:07:43,255 --> 00:07:44,614
But you reject my help so thoroughly.

139
00:07:44,935 --> 00:07:45,534
Forget it.

140
00:07:45,855 --> 00:07:46,614
Goodbye.

141
00:07:52,295 --> 00:07:53,734
Stop pretending to be weak.

142
00:07:54,055 --> 00:07:55,254
Get up and talk properly.

143
00:08:02,175 --> 00:08:02,814
Concubine.

144
00:08:04,615 --> 00:08:05,974
pəjjnd

145
00:08:06,495 --> 00:08:08,054
Why blame me?

146
00:08:12,095 --> 00:08:13,334
This lead

147
00:08:13,575 --> 00:08:14,774
is a huge secret.

148
00:08:15,015 --> 00:08:16,414
That wouldn't be good

149
00:08:16,415 --> 00:08:17,374
if someone overheard.

150
00:08:22,295 --> 00:08:23,494
Then how about this distance?

151
00:08:24,535 --> 00:08:25,454
Is it close enough?

152
00:08:29,415 --> 00:08:30,094
Concubine.

153
00:08:31,375 --> 00:08:34,094
Do you have any sexy, alluring clothes?

154
00:08:39,175 --> 00:08:40,494
Do you have any?

155
00:08:42,175 --> 00:08:44,614
[The Zhou family's wharf]

156
00:09:21,655 --> 00:09:22,414
Does it look good?

157
00:09:22,415 --> 00:09:23,214
Looks good.

158
00:09:28,495 --> 00:09:29,454
He's right.

159
00:09:36,255 --> 00:09:37,774
What were you doing on the night

160
00:09:38,215 --> 00:09:39,014
before the Spring Festival three years ago?

161
00:09:39,175 --> 00:09:40,094
Who could remember

162
00:09:40,135 --> 00:09:40,934
something from three years ago?

163
00:09:48,975 --> 00:09:49,694
I knew it.

164
00:09:49,695 --> 00:09:50,614
I just knew it.

165
00:09:51,335 --> 00:09:52,334
She'll

166
00:09:52,455 --> 00:09:54,334
surely seek revenge on us.

167
00:09:56,975 --> 00:09:57,854
Who?

168
00:09:58,175 --> 00:09:59,774
That actress, An He.

169
00:10:00,095 --> 00:10:01,574
She's now the Marshal's favorite.

170
00:10:01,815 --> 00:10:03,334
How could she possibly let us off?

171
00:10:03,455 --> 00:10:04,254
Explain clearly.

172
00:10:04,695 --> 00:10:05,814
Why would she

173
00:10:06,335 --> 00:10:07,334
seek revenge on you?

174
00:10:07,575 --> 00:10:08,654
It was all the Second Young Master.

175
00:10:09,095 --> 00:10:10,654
The Second Young Master sent us.

176
00:10:11,175 --> 00:10:12,694
The Second Young Master's men ordered us.

177
00:10:12,695 --> 00:10:14,414
to teach that actress a lesson.

178
00:10:15,055 --> 00:10:16,694
What does "teach a lesson" mean?

179
00:10:16,975 --> 00:10:19,574
What else? Assault her!

180
00:10:20,535 --> 00:10:23,094
Five... five or six night watchmen went.

181
00:10:23,295 --> 00:10:24,294
Six or seven...

182
00:10:27,175 --> 00:10:28,414
You beasts!

183
00:10:28,535 --> 00:10:30,214
Beasts!

184
00:10:31,695 --> 00:10:32,454
Don't hit me!

185
00:10:33,695 --> 00:10:34,694
Stop!

186
00:10:41,295 --> 00:10:42,374
This is very likely

187
00:10:42,375 --> 00:10:43,654
the reason why An He cut ties with Chuxue

188
00:10:43,655 --> 00:10:45,374
and left Wu County years ago.

189
00:10:46,535 --> 00:10:47,454
I never imagined

190
00:10:47,935 --> 00:10:48,934
Zhou Yichen would do

191
00:10:48,935 --> 00:10:50,014
something so despicable.

192
00:10:50,295 --> 00:10:52,014
You were fooled by his appearance.

193
00:10:52,215 --> 00:10:53,494
He's always been like this.

194
00:10:54,815 --> 00:10:56,174
What's that noise in the alley?

195
00:10:56,694 --> 00:10:57,414
I'm here!

196
00:10:57,415 --> 00:10:59,134
Help! Help!

197
00:11:00,215 --> 00:11:01,174
Split up!
- Over there!

198
00:11:01,175 --> 00:11:02,294
East side cargo just left port.

199
00:11:02,295 --> 00:11:02,934
No one's there.

200
00:11:02,935 --> 00:11:04,214
I'l lure them to the west.

201
00:11:04,694 --> 00:11:05,454
Leave it to me.

202
00:11:05,575 --> 00:11:06,214
A Liang!

203
00:11:06,335 --> 00:11:06,854
Watch out!

204
00:11:06,855 --> 00:11:07,934
A Liang!

205
00:11:08,694 --> 00:11:09,654
A Liang, are you there?

206
00:11:36,735 --> 00:11:37,614
Elder Brother.

207
00:11:37,694 --> 00:11:38,854
What is it, younger brother?

208
00:11:39,375 --> 00:11:40,494
As the eldest brother,

209
00:11:40,495 --> 00:11:42,574
I've come to check on the family business.

210
00:11:43,095 --> 00:11:44,014
So you won't keep saying

211
00:11:44,015 --> 00:11:45,374
I'm an idle loafer at home.

212
00:11:46,895 --> 00:11:48,214
Do you really think I'd believe

213
00:11:48,215 --> 00:11:49,054
such words from you?

214
00:11:49,775 --> 00:11:50,414
Elder Brother.

215
00:11:50,694 --> 00:11:52,174
The docks are crowded and chaotic.

216
00:11:53,095 --> 00:11:55,014
You came here alone and unguarded.

217
00:11:56,255 --> 00:11:57,854
What if something happens?

218
00:12:01,895 --> 00:12:03,134
Put out the fire! Hurry!

219
00:12:03,375 --> 00:12:04,814
Fire!

220
00:12:08,775 --> 00:12:09,774
With me accompanying him,

221
00:12:09,975 --> 00:12:11,814
he will certainly be safe.

222
00:12:26,735 --> 00:12:27,814
Fifth concubine?

223
00:12:31,694 --> 00:12:32,854
We're all family.

224
00:12:33,455 --> 00:12:35,254
Pointing guns at each other like this isn't right.

225
00:12:40,135 --> 00:12:41,854
I was just joking with him.

226
00:12:44,455 --> 00:12:45,454
You all head back.

227
00:12:53,215 --> 00:12:54,094
You've worked hard, little brother.

228
00:12:54,975 --> 00:12:55,734
After you're done,

229
00:12:56,335 --> 00:12:57,454
come home early for dinner.

230
00:13:19,055 --> 00:13:19,854
What's that?

231
00:13:19,935 --> 00:13:21,014
Change before heading back.

232
00:13:21,455 --> 00:13:22,374
Your clothes are torn.

233
00:13:25,375 --> 00:13:25,934
You change first.

234
00:13:25,935 --> 00:13:26,614
I'll wait outside.

235
00:13:26,615 --> 00:13:27,214
No need.

236
00:13:28,095 --> 00:13:29,054
Just don't look back.

237
00:13:41,655 --> 00:13:42,894
But you really have some nerve.

238
00:13:43,535 --> 00:13:44,854
After all this time,

239
00:13:45,015 --> 00:13:46,054
you can still dig up information.

240
00:13:48,655 --> 00:13:50,334
As the eldest son of the Zhou family,

241
00:13:50,815 --> 00:13:51,614
I have

242
00:13:51,655 --> 00:13:53,174
my own ways of getting information.

243
00:14:01,015 --> 00:14:02,014
Today's incident

244
00:14:02,455 --> 00:14:04,174
will surely prompt action from Zhou Yichen.

245
00:14:08,575 --> 00:14:10,414
[The Zhou family's wharf]

246
00:14:10,695 --> 00:14:11,294
Wang!

247
00:14:12,495 --> 00:14:13,134
What is it?

248
00:14:13,255 --> 00:14:13,894
Look at those,

249
00:14:13,895 --> 00:14:14,854
are they people?

250
00:14:16,975 --> 00:14:17,334
They are.

251
00:14:17,455 --> 00:14:18,254
They're our men.

252
00:14:18,335 --> 00:14:19,094
Report to the police station!

253
00:14:19,095 --> 00:14:19,814
Go, hurry!

254
00:14:20,175 --> 00:14:21,934
You must seek justice for us!

255
00:14:22,135 --> 00:14:22,774
Uncle,

256
00:14:22,775 --> 00:14:23,574
[Zhou Quan, the Chief of Police]

257
00:14:23,615 --> 00:14:24,494
thank you for

258
00:14:25,295 --> 00:14:26,334
handling this.

259
00:14:27,895 --> 00:14:29,574
We're family; no need for formalities.

260
00:14:39,615 --> 00:14:40,454
Come in, come in.

261
00:14:43,615 --> 00:14:44,254
Sir,

262
00:14:44,895 --> 00:14:47,214
five drowned bodies were just delivered from the docks.

263
00:14:47,535 --> 00:14:48,694
The cause of death is suspicious.

264
00:14:49,015 --> 00:14:50,294
I request additional personnel

265
00:14:50,535 --> 00:14:51,374
to investigate the docks.

266
00:14:51,495 --> 00:14:52,614
There should be clues.

267
00:14:52,895 --> 00:14:53,614
Shi'an,

268
00:14:54,575 --> 00:14:57,254
several accidents happen every day.

269
00:14:57,495 --> 00:14:59,094
As for drowning victims,

270
00:14:59,095 --> 00:15:00,814
what could be suspicious?

271
00:15:00,815 --> 00:15:02,414
But five people dying

272
00:15:02,975 --> 00:15:04,734
at the same location and time?

273
00:15:05,375 --> 00:15:06,654
Isn't that too coincidental?

274
00:15:06,975 --> 00:15:08,494
I don't find it coincidental at all.

275
00:15:09,455 --> 00:15:10,334
Probably

276
00:15:10,335 --> 00:15:11,814
they were drinking together yesterday.

277
00:15:11,815 --> 00:15:12,534
Got drunk,

278
00:15:12,535 --> 00:15:13,734
walked by the river,

279
00:15:13,735 --> 00:15:14,974
and someone fell in.

280
00:15:15,095 --> 00:15:16,654
Then others tried to rescue them.

281
00:15:16,655 --> 00:15:17,454
One after another,

282
00:15:17,455 --> 00:15:18,014
each trying to save the next,

283
00:15:18,015 --> 00:15:18,894
but failing,

284
00:15:18,895 --> 00:15:20,654
they all drowned.

285
00:15:20,655 --> 00:15:21,294
Right?

286
00:15:22,175 --> 00:15:22,814
Sir.

287
00:15:24,895 --> 00:15:27,174
Times are chaotic now.

288
00:15:27,815 --> 00:15:29,734
It's not our place to uphold justice.

289
00:15:32,015 --> 00:15:33,334
Take this money

290
00:15:33,615 --> 00:15:35,534
to compensate the families.

291
00:15:35,815 --> 00:15:37,294
Stop the commotion at the station.

292
00:15:37,295 --> 00:15:38,454
It's giving me a headache.

293
00:15:39,255 --> 00:15:39,814
Go on.

294
00:15:42,975 --> 00:15:43,534
But this case...

295
00:15:43,535 --> 00:15:45,094
This is an order,

296
00:15:45,095 --> 00:15:46,734
not a discussion.

297
00:15:47,455 --> 00:15:48,894
If you can't handle it,

298
00:15:49,175 --> 00:15:50,534
don't come back tomorrow.

299
00:16:08,135 --> 00:16:08,974
Captain Yu.

300
00:16:13,095 --> 00:16:14,094
Zhou?

301
00:16:14,375 --> 00:16:15,254
What do you want?

302
00:16:15,535 --> 00:16:17,094
I came to ask for your help.

303
00:16:17,815 --> 00:16:18,414
What help?

304
00:16:18,815 --> 00:16:20,814
Five workers died at my family's dock.

305
00:16:22,135 --> 00:16:23,294
The case is closed.

306
00:16:23,815 --> 00:16:24,734
It was an accident.

307
00:16:24,975 --> 00:16:26,574
Isn't it strange that anywhere near water,

308
00:16:26,855 --> 00:16:29,094
on or off the estate, seems prone to "accidents"?

309
00:16:30,855 --> 00:16:32,454
You must have many clues.

310
00:16:33,575 --> 00:16:34,294
Young Master Zhou,

311
00:16:35,455 --> 00:16:36,894
you yourself are part of the Zhou family.

312
00:16:37,695 --> 00:16:39,134
If there are any doubts

313
00:16:40,975 --> 00:16:42,094
you can go back and investigate.
